cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.VR 

The paper presents a novel method for connecting data on the visualization level, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and data management (cs.DB). The use of visualization methods such as graphs, tag clouds, maps, and timelines suggests a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the mention of combining diverse data structures through a mouse click implies a potential application in virtual reality (cs.VR).
